The general polynomial
p(x)=x^{n}-s_{1}x^{n-1}+s_{2}x^{n-2}+…+(-1)^{n}s_{n}
over the field \mathbb {F}(s_{1},s_{2},…,s_{n}) generated by the Elementary Symmetric Functions is separable with Galois group S_{n}.

The regular n-gon is constructible with a ruler and compass if and only if n is a power of 2 multiplied by a product of Fermat primes, i.e.,
n=2^{k}p_{1}(…)p_{r}
where p_{i}=2^{2^{c}}+1 where c\in \mathbb {N} is some number.

